### Pattern 9: Layout Gate (Access Control in Layout)
**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/layout.tsx:40-79`

The only existing gate pattern is the org access check in `[slug]/layout.tsx`:

```ts
export default async function OrgLayout({ children, params }: OrgLayoutProps) {
  const { slug } = await params;

  let hasAccess = true;
  try {
    await requireOrgAccess(slug);
  } catch (error) {
    log.debug("[org-layout] access denied", { slug, error: parseError(error) });
    hasAccess = false;
  }
  if (!hasAccess) {
    notFound();   // ← redirects to 404
  }

  return (
    <HydrateClient>
      {children}
    </HydrateClient>
  );
}
```

The access helper is defined in `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/lib/org-access-clerk.ts`. It calls `auth()` → `clerkClient().organizations.getOrganization({ slug })` → `getUserOrgMemberships(userId)` to verify membership.

There is no existing "show different UI based on feature state" gate component — the only conditional layout pattern uses `notFound()` for hard blocking.

